                                                            <li class="menu__item is-leaf leaf"><a href="/en/taxonomy/term/2544" title="Perhaps Britain&amp;#39;s greatest contribution to the world is not art or technology or sport, but the English language itself. Great Britain is home to the first language of business, science and travel. The story of English begins more than a thousand years ago, but its global importance means it is still making history now.

